hpnicfDot11LIC.name: hpnicfDot11LIC

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11LIC.description: This MIB provides information for WLAN license configuration in AC. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. Basic Service Set The IEEE 802.11 BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. It will be identified by BSSID.

hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroupSupport.name: hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroupSupport
hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroupSupport.description: Represents support hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroup 'ture': device spport hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroup. 'false': device not spport hpnicfDot11LicApNumGroupp.

hpnicfDot11LICDefautAPNumPermit.name: hpnicfDot11LICDefautAPNumPermit
hpnicfDot11LICDefautAPNumPermit.description: Represents the number of AP connection permitted for one AC without license.

hpnicfDot11LICCurrentAPNumPermit.name: hpnicfDot11LICCurrentAPNumPermit
hpnicfDot11LICCurrentAPNumPermit.description: Represents the total number of AP connection permitted for one AC, include default number and the licenses that installed.

hpnicfDot11LICMaxAPNumPermit.name: hpnicfDot11LICMaxAPNumPermit
hpnicfDot11LICMaxAPNumPermit.description: Represents the maximum number of AP to support connection permitted for one AC, include default number and full licenses.

hpnicfDot11LICApNumLicTable.name: hpnicfDot11LICApNumLicTable

hpnicfDot11LICApNumLicEntry.name: hpnicfDot11LICApNumLicEntry

hpnicfDot11LICApNum.name: hpnicfDot11LICApNum
hpnicfDot11LICApNum.description: Represents support connect ap number of the license.

hpnicfDot11LICFeatureAttrTable.name: hpnicfDot11LICFeatureAttrTable

hpnicfDot11LICFeatureAttrEntry.name: hpnicfDot11LICFeatureAttrEntry

hpnicfDot11LICAttrDefVal.name: hpnicfDot11LICAttrDefVal

hpnicfDot11LICAttrMaxVal.name: hpnicfDot11LICAttrMaxVal
hpnicfDot11LICAttrMaxVal.description: Represents the maximum value of the license type.

hpnicfDot11LICFeatureLicTable.name: hpnicfDot11LICFeatureLicTable
hpnicfDot11LICFeatureLicTable.description: Each entry contains license information of wlan feature.

hpnicfDot11LICFeatureLicEntry.name: hpnicfDot11LICFeatureLicEntry

hpnicfDot11LICTypeName.name: hpnicfDot11LICTypeName

hpnicfDot11LICTimeLimit.name: hpnicfDot11LICTimeLimit
hpnicfDot11LICTimeLimit.description: Represents available time left of the license entry.

hpnicfDot11LICValue.name: hpnicfDot11LICValue
hpnicfDot11LICValue.description: Represents the value of the license entry. If hpnicfDot11LICFeatureTypeName is 'AP', this meaning of ap number, and so no.
